\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
## Read in the data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
Let's read in the data with the following commands:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
```{r load} library(readxl)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
download.file("https://ryanwomack.com/data/PharmaDemo.xls", "mydata.xls")
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
mydata<-read_excel("mydata.xls")
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
names(mydata)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
attach(mydata)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
```
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
## Describe the Data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
Then we will get some summary statistics on the Age and Weight variables:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
```{r summary} summary(Age)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
summary(Weight) ```
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
Now plot the data:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
```{r plot, echo=FALSE} library(ggplot2)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
ggplot(mydata, aes(Weight, Age))+ geom_point() ```
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
## Regression
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
```{r regression} summary(lm(Age~Weight))
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
ggplot(mydata, aes(Weight, Age))+ geom_point()+ stat_smooth() ```
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size scriptsize
All done!
